Tilkal is a MUD source code. It is dedicated to everybody who wants to
put up a MUD without pain.

# Build:

The project now uses CMake instead of the legacy Perl script that generated
makefiles.

The default build stays on a broadly compatible C++11 profile. A first
single-partition C++20 module preview exists for the bans subsystem, but it is
kept experimental because the current WSL toolchain in this workspace is GCC
9.4 and cannot build standard modules.

Requirements:

    cmake
    g++

Configure:

    cmake -S . -B build -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Debug

Build:

    cmake --build build

Release build:

    cmake -S . -B build-release -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release
    cmake --build build-release

Experimental modules build on a recent toolchain only:

    cmake -S . -B build-modules -DTILKAL_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_MODULES=ON
    cmake --build build-modules

Docker image build:

    docker build -t tilkal .

